comments.comment:
Hi Padi, can you say more about what you are expecting to see and what disappears? I see that you’re building a new categorical array, so only categorical variables are eligible for being included in the new array variable. What do you mean by the ‘crunch menu’?
Mike

Hi Mike,





The surprising behavior for me is to see large numbers of items in the lefthand crunch menu disappear entirely. I discussed with others involved with the project and we think there should be more variables eligible to build into array or multiple response
 than the few that appear after clicking on these options. Screenshots to describe:












Padi
Hallam Joseph, Ph.D.

Senior Project Director 








805 Veterans Blvd. Suite 202, 



Redwood City, CA 94063



T: 650-319-0708 | F: 650-462-8422 | M: 650-260-3405



Padi.Joseph@yougov.com



http://www.yougov.com

What we are trying to do is combine two multiple response variables with the same response options but asked of different populations into one variable so we can show the client the combined % of people answering a certain category like "Don't like or trust
 Google." We are doing this through R by combining weighted counts for now but want the client to be able to recreate it easily on their own. This can be done by someone like Rebecca but she is extremely busy so I expected I could do it in the GUI somehow.
